      "span_text": "Carbon and oxygen corelevel spectroscopy, in particular X-ray absorption spectroscopy (XAS), is a very sensitive probe of the local electronic structure as well as chemical composition and local bonding environment, which has been applied in several studies of reduced graphene oxides. In this work, XAS is employed to study the surface properties of the individual oxides and the nanocomposites, and the sensitivity of XAS to the local environment is used to identify the various carbon bonding environments."
